## ESPHome / Home Assistant Voice PE

This project uses the `voice_kit` component from ESPHome's 
[home-assistant-voice-pe](https://github.com/esphome/home-assistant-voice-pe) 
repository, which is licensed under the ESPHome License.

The ESPHome License consists of:
- MIT License for Python codebase and other parts
- GPLv3 License for C++/runtime codebase (file extensions .c, .cpp, .h, .hpp, .tcc, .ino)

See the license at: https://github.com/esphome/home-assistant-voice-pe/blob/dev/LICENSE

**Note on GPLv3 Compliance:**

The `voice_kit` component contains C++ code licensed under GPLv3. Since this 
component is used as an external dependency (downloaded at compile time) and 
not directly copied into this repository, the GPLv3 license applies to the 
compiled firmware that includes this component. When distributing compiled 
firmware images, you must comply with GPLv3 requirements, including 
providing access to the source code of the GPLv3-licensed components.

